DESCRIPTION
***********
A collection of bash functions that composes an API for administrating CentOS Server linux boxes.
i.e. provisioning websites, installing services, hardening daemons, etc.

FILE USAGE
**********
sudo -s
source <file> <parameters>, i.e. source networking.sh
<function>
exit

DAEMON INSTALLATION GUIDELINES
******************************
01. Install prerequisites
02. Create user & group
03. Donwload, compile & install files
04. Make binaries availiable to PATH
05. Configure
06. Set logs
07. Integrate into logrotate
08. Set daemon
09. Set firewall
10. Collect garbage

THERE IS A PLACE FOR EVERYTHING
*******************************
/opt : Installation directory, i.e. /etc/mysql
/etc : Configuration files (.conf), i.e. /etc/mysql/my.conf
/var/log : Log files (.log), i.e. /etc/mysql/error.log
/var/run : PID files (.pid) | Lock files (.lock) | Socket files (.sock), i.e. /var/run/mysql/mysql.pid
